## agenc tmux resolve-mission

Resolve a tmux pane to its mission UUID

### Synopsis

Looks up which mission is running in the given tmux pane.

Prints the mission UUID to stdout if found, or prints nothing if no active
mission is associated with the pane. Always exits with code 0.

This command is used internally by tmux keybindings to determine the focused
mission.

```
agenc tmux resolve-mission <pane-id> [flags]
```

### Options

```
  -h, --help   help for resolve-mission
```
